In this project We have created A hardware system comprising of ESP32,DHT22, MQ135, GP2Y1010AU0F and anion generator. 
The sensors will sense temperature, humidity, gas, and dust density. 
The ESP itself will calculate the AQI and send out a signal through BLE in the form of temperature, humidity, AQI, and anion generator status(0 or 1). 
Our aim is to create an application which will receive this BLE string after connection with the device and display the data in a user-friendly format. 
The application will also send a signal to the ESP to start or stop the anion generator. 
The application, on receiving the values through BLE, is displaying them beautifully on the application dashboard We'll send the AQI to the Firebase backend database and store it there. 
Let us not worry so much about the UI and just work on functionality, providing a Bluetooth connection, receiving the values, and sending them to the Firebase backend first, we will work on the UI later. 